\frac{dB}{d\eta}=\frac{B}{2}-\frac{B^3}{8}-\frac{A^2 B}{8}-\frac{k}{2} B \sin T+\frac{k}{2} A \cos T
\end{eqnarray}
Linearizing (\ref{Aeq2}) and (\ref{Beq2}) about the origin and looking for the condition where Hopf bifurcation takes place, we find:

